Annotation key management commands.

USAGE:
  scw annotations key <command>

AVAILABLE COMMANDS:
  create      Create an annotation key.
  delete      Delete a key definition. Fails if the key has any associated values.
  get         Retrieve a specific key.
  list        List of keys.
  update      Update name or description. All associated resources will immediately display the new name.

FLAGS:
  -h, --help                help for key
      --list-sub-commands   List all subcommands

GLOBAL FLAGS:
  -c, --config string    The path to the config file
  -D, --debug            Enable debug mode
  -o, --output string    Output format: json or human, see 'scw help output' for more info (default "human")
  -p, --profile string   The config profile to use

Use "scw annotations key [command] --help" for more information about a command.
